jobs_results.description:
Smadex is a cutting-edge ad-tech company: we process more than 2.5 million ad requests per second, replying under 100ms. Every day we generate several TBs of data that need to be processed, analyzed, and aggregated, so our real-time components get smarter every day. We need you to help us keep our platform in motion, so if you like challenges and enjoy owning your code from design to production, this is meant for you. Keep reading!

This position is based in Barcelona.
Role Overview

We are looking for an iOS Engineer who will be at the forefront of building our Ads SDK. In this role, you will enable publishers (app developers) to effectively optimize and monetize their iOS apps through advanced advertising solutions.
The Opportunity:
‚Ä¢ Design and develop an iOS Ads SDK.
‚Ä¢ Keep the SDK current with the latest iOS advancements as well as new technologies and industry trends across leading app platforms.
‚Ä¢ Provide integration support for customers and maintain detailed, user-friendly SDK documentation.
‚Ä¢ Work closely with cross-functional teams across our tech team to ensure the SDK seamlessly integrates with the Smadex platform.
Requirements and Qualifications:
‚Ä¢ 3+ years of experience as a Software Engineer.
‚Ä¢ Significant experience with iOS development with Swift and Objective-C.
‚Ä¢ In-depth knowledge of multithreading, networking, and the internals of iOS, including optimization for performance and power efficiency.
‚Ä¢ A strong passion for mobile platforms and a commitment to staying current with the latest iOS advancements.
Bonus Points:
‚Ä¢ Experience building and distributing CocoaPods or Swift Packages.
‚Ä¢ Knowledge of mobile advertising technologies such as MRAID and VAST.
‚Ä¢ Experience building and distributing React Native and/or Unity plugins for iOS.

Please note that we do NOT provide VISA sponsorship. Candidates without a legal permit to work in Spain won't be considered.
What Will You Do at Smadex?
‚Ä¢ Be the go-to person for iOS development in the company.
‚Ä¢ Be an advocate of our ‚ÄúYou build it, you run it‚Äù philosophy: you will own your code from design to production; testing, deploying, and monitoring. You will learn from every step in the software development process.
‚Ä¢ Participate in code reviews, contribute to technical and architectural decisions, collaborate in a fast-paced environment where every opinion counts.
If you become a member of our team, you will get the chance to:
‚Ä¢ Have a real impact on one of the hottest ad-tech companies in Barcelona and Europe.
‚Ä¢ Be part of an agile team with a strong focus on innovation and technology, to continue improving your knowledge in the field.
‚Ä¢ Work in a multicultural, young & talented environment with people from more than 28 different nationalities!
‚Ä¢ Enjoy benefits such as a monthly ticket restaurant allowance, flexible working hours, DIR gym membership, LinkedIn Learning, daily fresh fruits & snacks, TGIF‚Äôs monthly activities, team-building events, and work anniversary celebrations.
‚Ä¢ And more!
